Sticky gears—Lister strikes again. They’re more jammed than the ship’s air vents after Cat’s hairspray spree. Grab a cloth and some cleaning fluid—don’t use Lister’s lager, tempting as it is. Wipe them down until they’re spinning again, smoother than Kryten’s polishing routine. I’d explain how gears work, but you’d probably nod off faster than Lister during a hygiene lecture.

